From the first time I downloaded the game I loved every bit of it. I thought the artwork was beautiful, the puzzles were a nice challenge, and the story was all around captivating until the end. I loved this because it's not like other Hidden Object games I have played before, it's not just about finding the missing piece to the 2D picture, but it's you're trying to solve a full fresh mystery!   I do enjoy playing this game and I highly recommend others to give it a try, but before I go I think I should bring up one problem that even I encountered recently while playing.  Some time after their update of this year some of the videos including the opening video won't play instead it skips the video completely.  I don't know if anyone else has had this problem but I know that it's NOT me skipping the video, and I guess I would just like it if someone could help me and maybe make a new update that fixes this problem because I really don't want my own solution to be to delete the game, THAT'S THE LAST THING I WANT TO DO!   Well that's all I had to say, I hope this review was helpful to the future puzzlers and the team of Big Fish. Happy playing and Bye! : )

This is a magnificent game. The graphics are just incredible. If you'd like a little adventure in Vermont in the autumn, buy "Enigmatis".  Unfortunately it is dark. The theme, the weather, the whole setting is dark. Why can't someone come up with a beautiful, CHEERFUL game??? Something that makes you feel good to play? That's the only reason I didn't give it 5 stars. Even "Letters From Nowhere" was slightly more cheerful than this one.  Give us magical knights on crusade (without blood and guts), or mystical kingdoms --- something less "dark", please. Never-the-less this is a truly great game, everything functions beautifully on my little Asus T. Pad. I look forward (cringingly) to "Enigmatis 2". Have fun folks, and thanks Big Fish. Well worth it. I find any game that requires you to chase back and forth between sites for clues or items to complete actions just plain boring.  It requires more time than intelligence and for my money is just a tool used to extend the life of a game.  Will never give 5 stars to a title that uses this tactic.For the most part, a puzzle should be self contained and solvable within the same scene in which it appears.  The old super Nintendo game, of which I just spoke, would be a great refresher for anyone concerned with creativity as much as they are the $.  Think outside the box.  Create something a player hates to put down and when it ends hates that it has ended even though it has taken them days or even weeks to get there.  Make something that's all you.  The $ are sure to follow.

This truly was a wonderful, quality game. It was full of clever puzzles, tons of hidden object scenes and mini-puzzles, suspense and mystery with a little bit of horror thrown in. It had a storyline that was easy to follow, beautifully rendered scenes and great detail The overall mood was dark and spooky- which I love in games. I played on expert because I don't like my hidden adventure games to be to easy and I don't want the game to point every little thing out to me, and I found that the puzzles, mini-games and the overall hidden objects had a perfect balance between challenging and fun. None were too hard to the point where I had to use a hint- but if you do find that one puzzle is giving you a harder time than you'd like, you can always just "Skip" it (after a certain amount of time has passed working on it. ) I'm the type of person though who loves to solve everything on their own, and I never had to skip anything. I did use th hint a few times outside of the mini-games, though only to point me in the direction I should be going next.  If you love creepy mystery games full of suspense, enjoy solving puzzles and putting the clues together, DEFINITELY check this one out!!!

I NEVER comment/rate games, this one deserves it. This is far more than a "Hidden Object" game (which I hate), there is actually a very INTRIGUING plot, MANY puzzle layers to it, LOTS of ground to cover (which you have to UNcover), in depth puzzles, lovely graphics and sound/music...Im impressed. Even when there was a hidden object puzzle, I was quite pleased that it wasnt timed, and there were no penalties for "mis-clicks". (plus, each HO puzzle left you with an "item" you needed to further solve the mystery) This game was genuinely fun, ineresting and stress-free. Its a definite"who-dunnit"...a little dark, made it exciting. Im being totally honest when I say it kept me up to continue playing, late at night. Dont expect weeks of fun, i finished the game in a few days....but thats because I couldnt stop playing.
